PlayFab · Limits

















PlayFab







Usage Limits
Use of PlayFab Game Services is free within certain usage limits. Default limits are set to avoid abuse, and may be easily upgraded based on each games's unique requirements.


To view the usage limits, create a free PlayFab account, and login to the PlayFab Game Manager. Visit the "Settings" page, then click on the "Limits" tab.
Please contact us if you have questions about limits.
Read more about limits












PlayFab · Jobs

















PlayFab







Join The PlayFab Team
PlayFab's mission is to transform the game industry by delivering a live-game operations platform that helps studios of all sizes more effectively build, launch, and operate their games post-launch.


Game operations — everything you do with your game post-launch — is hard, and getting harder. The gap in best practices between the best developers and everyone else is large. We're helping to close that gap by providing everything a developer needs to be successful — all the tools, technologies, and know-how — allowing developers to go back to focusing on their game, and letting us take care of everything else.
PlayFab recently received Series A funding from Benchmark and Madrona Venture Group. New hires should expect to hit the ground running and make significant contributions from day one. We don't have a kegerator or dogs running around the office; we do have a seasoned and mature team committed to changing the game industry for the better.














PlayFab · Style Guide

















PlayFab







Style Guide
PlayFab makes hard things easy. Our voice is bright, bold, and intentional. We care about details and clarity. This style guide will help you use our brand assets, like our logo and colors, in a way that is consistent with our promised level of power and reliability.


PlayFab Logos


Powered by PlayFab logo: use for games running on the PlayFab platform. Include this in a prominent location in your game, such as a splash screen.
PlayFab logo: use on your website or marketing materials.
Download PlayFab logos (ZIP)







Copyright and credit notice
Please include this copyright and credit notice as is, without modification, on any "help" or "credit" screens in your game.
Portions of this program (c) 2017 PlayFab, Inc.


Logo Usage Guidelines


Clear space

The height/width of the Logomark is a measurement for the minimum clear space requirement around the logo. This space is flat and free of any other design element and clear of the edge of the page.


Minimum size

Screen
The minimum size for screen display is 120px x 33px
Print
The minimum size for print display is 0.8”x0.22”
The logo should never be sized below the above dimensions. For dimensions smaller than 160px x 45px or 1.1” x 0.3”, please use the alternate small display logo provided.




Color options
Color usage for this logo is restricted. The logo can only be presented using the specified "PlayFab Orange" as documented below, or in tints of black when color is unavailable. If using gray, do not go below 40% black.
PlayFab Orange

						PANTONE: ORANGE 021 U
						 CMYK: 0 , 70, 100, 0
						 RGB: 256, 109, 33
						 HEX: #ff6d21
					
Acceptable uses



Primary



Reverse (orange)



Black



Reverse (black)



Gray (60%) - ok



Reverse (gray - 40%) - ok



Reverse (gray - 25%) - too light


Unacceptable uses
Unacceptable uses also apply to black and white logo applications.



Do not switch the specified colors in the logo



Do not choose arbitrary colors or use tints for the logo



Do not stretch or skew the logo



Do not outline the logo



Do not change the composition of the logo



Do not substitute a different typeface for the logo



Don't alter or switch out the text



Don't combine unrelated graphics and/or text with the logo lockup



Do not separate or use the logomark without the accompanying text












PlayFab, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 6:04 AM ET
Internet Software and Services

Company Overview of PlayFab, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
PlayFab, Inc. provides a backend platform for games that deliver real-time tools and services for LiveOps. It offers its services for live mobile, PC, and console games. The company enables users to build card, multiplayer shooter, VR experience, and Facebook games. It also provide add-ons for categories, such as advertising, analytics, community, customer support, content management, marketing, monetization, migration kits, multiplayer, platforms, and other services. PlayFab, Inc. was formerly known as UberNet Inc. and changed its name to PlayFab, Inc. The company was founded in 2011 and is based in Seattle, Washington with a location in Berlin, Germany.


