PlayFab API Documentation

		If you prefer not to use our available SDKs, you can access the entire PlayFab service directly via these REST-like Web APIs.
		For simplicity and security, all function calls are HTTP POST requests over SSL, and all data is formatted as JSON with optional gzip encoding.
	


Client
APIs which provide the full range of PlayFab features available to the client - authentication, account and data management, inventory, friends, matchmaking, reporting, and platform-specific functionality


Server
Provides functionality to allow external (developer-controlled) servers to interact with user inventories and data in a trusted manner, and to handle matchmaking and client connection orchestration


Matchmaker
Enables the use of an external match-making service in conjunction with PlayFab hosted Game Server instances


Admin
APIs for managing title configurations, uploaded Game Server code executables, and user data






















